      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Economically, a surge in low-skilled, undocumented labor can depress wages for native-born workers competing for the same jobs, effectively undermining the economic stability of the working class. Socially, unchecked migration places immense, unsustainable strain on local public infrastructure, including schools, healthcare, and emergency services, which are not funded to handle rapid population influxes. Moreover, a lack of clear legal pathways can erode social cohesion by creating parallel societies and undermining the shared civic values of the nation.",
      "source": "target",
